---
layout: base
title: The Thought Experiment Library
description: Classic thought experiments given serious popular treatment — what they were designed to show, what they actually show, and what remains genuinely unresolved.
permalink: /thought-experiments/
---

<div class="container" style="padding-top: var(--space-12); padding-bottom: var(--space-20);">

  <header class="project-section-header">
    <nav class="breadcrumbs" aria-label="Breadcrumb">
      <ol class="breadcrumbs__list">
        <li class="breadcrumbs__item"><a class="breadcrumbs__link" href="/">Home</a></li>
        <li class="breadcrumbs__item"><a class="breadcrumbs__link" href="/projects/">Projects</a></li>
        <li class="breadcrumbs__item breadcrumbs__item--current" aria-current="page">Thought Experiments</li>
      </ol>
    </nav>
    <span class="section-badge section-badge--thought-experiments">Thought Experiments</span>
    <h1>The Thought Experiment Library</h1>
    <p class="project-section-lede">A thought experiment is philosophy's most elegant tool: a scenario stripped to the essential, designed to force a choice. The best ones don't dissolve when examined — they get harder. Here they receive the treatment they deserve: precise, honest, and unsatisfied with easy answers.</p>
    <p style="font-family: var(--font-ui); font-size: var(--text-sm); margin-top: var(--space-4);">
      Know a thought experiment we should cover? <a href="/thought-experiments/submit/" style="color: var(--color-link); font-weight: 600;">Suggest it</a>
    </p>
    <div style="margin-top:var(--space-4);display:flex;gap:var(--space-3);flex-wrap:wrap;">
      <a href="/thought-experiments/showcase/" class="btn">Showcase</a>
    </div>
  </header>

  <div class="te-grid">
    {% for experiment in collections["thought-experiments"] %}
    <article class="te-card">
      <header>
        <p class="te-card__meta">{{ experiment.data.philosopher }} · {{ experiment.data.yearProposed }}</p>
        <h2 class="te-card__title"><a href="{{ experiment.url }}">{{ experiment.data.title }}</a></h2>
      </header>
      <p class="te-card__description">{{ experiment.data.description }}</p>
      <a href="{{ experiment.url }}" class="te-card__link">Examine the argument →</a>
    </article>
    {% endfor %}
  </div>

</div>
